Outside the dreadlands are a barren wasteland, and the golden sun quietly sets behind the ice-capped mountains.  An erie sensation overcomes me.  Flames dance in my left hand as water drips from underneath my fingernails of my right hand.  Each step I take molds a new foothold in the earth, and the wind is at my back in any direction I choose.  I sense the elements are trying to communicate, as if they are trying to forewarn me of a danger.  Yet the Tundra Yeti reluctantly look my way in fear of my pursuit, and the giants retreat to their strongholds in view of my presence.  I conjure a staff to assist me in my journey, and grasp it tightly with my right hand.  Water runs down the rough edges of the wood, striking the ground with force, and disappears.  Saddened by the recent death of Jabanik, I am hesitant to mold another pet, and continue to walk alone.  I set forth to the ruined druid rings, in hoping a kind druid would call upon the winds to carry me away... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uelynwinterspice.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elynwinterspice</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Master</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/16/02 10:49:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   re</span><hr size=1> Bravo old friend!<br>
