I sit in the midst of the giant wasteland, and search through my dusty spellbook, my legs folded under one another.  I eagerly flip page by page, in search of what would lift a great burden off of my back.  Finally, I find it, my 49th Season fire pet.  A provider of heat, an intellect at mind, and a warrior at heart.  I rise to my feet, and dig my Golden Efreeti Boots into the ground to better brace myself.  I close my eyes, and chant.  I bring my arms out to my sides, and stretch my fingers far apart.  Green electricity sparks from my fingertips, and grow in size.  The golden sun flashes brightly, and disappears behind the clouds.  Suddenly before me, it is a mass of gas and energy, and a fire elemental floats in front of me.  &quot;Following you, master,&quot; he explains, and with that he is silent.  The heat radiating from all sides melts the snow around him, revealing a floor of dead grass and mud.  His flames feel good against my skin, and I feel replenished by his energy.  We continue to the rings together, with his bright form illuminating the path for me.  I stride with a more comfortable aura, knowing I once again have a valiant companion by my side, and we continue over the ice capped mountains together... <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=291365</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/udidrika2001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Didrika2001</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.free-graphics.com/gallery2/3danimations/flags/tn_16.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><br><font color=#0000FF>!!!BEWARE!!!</font></br><br><u><b>I have multiple personalities</b></u></br></span><br>  Posts: 332<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/30/02 10:38:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re</span><hr size=1> Your good - You keep each one short but interesting.... I wish I could write like that - but I suck at it hehe (I tried) <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>"People may not remember exactly what you did, or what you said ~BUT~ they will always remember how you made them feel."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/uciniminiteenytiny.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cinimini Teenytiny</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>THogg's Lubba</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/31/02 9:43:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   The Endless Journey</span><hr size=1> I write this with pain in my heart:<br>
<br>
     I continue my walk with Gobn with hate in my soul.  An undying pain grasps my throat, and makes it difficult to breathe.  I travel with a glare in my eye, and a scowl is worn on my lips.  I look upon every mob that walks across my plane of view.  Death, destruction and chaos race through my head, and my brain begins to ache.  Why did I have this pain in my heart?  What caused my hands to shake so?  My stomach roared with hunger, and I saw Gobn grow more impatient with each stride.  I becaume frusterated with my headache, hunger and shortness of air.  A rage overcame me, and set a path to end all life to which was before me.<br>
     My eyes turned red with fury as I turned toward a Tundri Yeti.  I equipped my pet with two golden modulation rods, and the jewels imbedded in the metals shinned brightly.  I cast a Burnout spell with caused him to have the same sense of rage as I did.  &quot;Taunting attacker, Master&quot; is all I could hear as his voice traveled off towards the Yeti.  In a flash, my pet was mercilessly beating on the Yeti, and between the crushes and kicks, deep red blood poured from the side of the monster.  The sight of vunerability only pleased my pet further, and heightened his rage.  Within seconds, the Yeti laid lifeless, and Gobn turned his flame covered back to him, and faithfully returned to my side to rest.  I watched the ordeal from a distance.  I gained a sick pleasure in watching the savage thrashing of the Tundri Yeti by my pet, and it lightly lifted my spirits once again.  But it wasn't enough, and I thirsted for more blood.  Quickly, one by one, the population of the Dreadlands decreased, with my twisted smile growing bigger and bigger.  Gobn became more and more determined to please me with each kill, and his attacks turned into a frenzy.  He drew his happiness from my satisfaction, and I drew my satisfaction from their deaths.<br>
     Hours later, the carnage ends.  I collapse to my knees after exhaustion overcomes me.  I pant heavily, and my breath drifts from my mouth, floats into the air and disappears.  Gobn floats by my side, tired, but content.  Tears begin to flow relentlessly from my eyes, and I quiver uncontrolably.  The ruthless rage had once again overcome me, and I was powerless to defend myself.  It was the 4th time it had happened to me in my 56 seasons, hoping that my age would eventually overcome my weakness.  However, I still bow to this overwhelming force.  After reflecting about my regret of the matter, I carry on... <p>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=291365</p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.showPrevMessage?topicID=41.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.showNextMessage?topicID=41.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=41.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/fr/themes/default/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.threadControl?topicID=41.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/fr/themes/default/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=41.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm11.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=41.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><fo